<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">US AA+</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What do you do with <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32274940.264413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDgtMDEvdXMtcmF0aW5nLXNsYXNoZWQtZnJvbS1hYWE=
tYnktZml0Y2gtaW4tZWNoby1vZi1zLXAtcy0yMDExLW1vdmU_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDgwMjIzX01PTk=
VZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09M=
jMwODAyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB27f6e7c6" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;">  this information</a>?</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fitch Ratings =E2=80=A6=C2=A0cut the US=E2=80=
=99s sovereign credit grade one level from AAA to AA+. The move comes just =
two months after it warned the rating was under threat as lawmakers flirted=
 with default by battling over raising the nation=E2=80=99s debt limit.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The credit grader justified the shift by argui=
ng the country=E2=80=99s finances will likely deteriorate over the next thr=
ee years given tax cuts, new spending initiatives, economic shocks and repe=
ated political gridlock.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Pushing back hours before her department is se=
t to ramp up its borrowing to plug a ballooning budget deficit, Treasury Se=
cretary Janet Yellen called the downgrade =E2=80=9Carbitrary=E2=80=9D and =
=E2=80=9Coutdated.=E2=80=9D The economy has recently shown signs of resilie=
nce and the debt limit was ultimately lifted, she noted.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One thing I suppose you could do is read <a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32274940.264413/aHR0cHM=
6Ly93d3cuZml0Y2hyYXRpbmdzLmNvbS9yZXNlYXJjaC9zb3ZlcmVpZ25zL2ZpdGNoLWRvd25ncm=
FkZXMtdW5pdGVkLXN0YXRlcy1sb25nLXRlcm0tcmF0aW5ncy10by1hYS1mcm9tLWFhYS1vdXRsb=
29rLXN0YWJsZS0wMS0wOC0yMDIz/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB19172bd7" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Fit=
ch=E2=80=99s note explaining the downgrade</a>, say =E2=80=9Chuh, yeah, the=
y make some good points,=E2=80=9D and trim your allocation to US Treasuries=
. =E2=80=9CThe rating downgrade of the United States reflects the expected =
fiscal deterioration over the next three years, a high and growing general =
government debt burden, and the erosion of governance relative to 'AA' and =
'AAA' rated peers over the last two decades that has manifested in repeated=
 debt limit standoffs and last-minute resolutions,=E2=80=9D says Fitch. It =
is a little weird that Fitch <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/32274940.264413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2Fy=
dGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDUtMjUvdGhlLXVzLW1pZ2h0LWJlLW9ubHktYWE_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDgwMjI=
zX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3=
Rlcm09MjMwODAyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9f1=
a095a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">  threatened to downgrade</a> the US in May, putting it on a=
 negative ratings watch because Congress had not yet worked out a debt-ceil=
ing deal and was running out of time, and then actually downgraded the US i=
n August after Congress=C2=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>work out the deal and averte=
d a near-term default, but I take their general point. =E2=80=9CIn Fitch's =
view, there has been a steady deterioration in standards of governance over=
 the last 20 years, including on fiscal and debt matters, notwithstanding t=
he June bipartisan agreement to suspend the debt limit until January 2025,=
=E2=80=9D fine.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And, look, the world is big and=C2=A0lots of p=
eople get their news from lots of different sources, and I am sure that the=
re are a few people who learned yesterday =E2=80=94=C2=A0from the Fitch not=
e or from news reports about the downgrade =E2=80=94=C2=A0that the US gover=
nment has a lot of debt and keeps doing pointless debt-ceiling standoffs th=
at could cause defaults. Not a ton of them are professional Treasury trader=
s, though. There is not a rush to dump Treasuries by investors who thought =
that they were super-safe but who found out, yesterday, from Fitch, that th=
ey are not.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-c=
olor: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Benjamin Purvis and Simon Kennedy <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32274940.264413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDgtMDEvdXMtcmF0aW5nLXNsYXNo=
ZWQtZnJvbS1hYWEtYnktZml0Y2gtaW4tZWNoby1vZi1zLXAtcy0yMDExLW1vdmU_Y21waWQ9QkJ=
EMDgwMjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZX=
ImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwODAyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cC27f6e7c6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">  write</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The bond market shrugged off the downgrade. Th=
e yield on 10-year Treasuries was little changed in the London session, whi=
le the equivalent rate on German securities fell modestly. Risk-sensitive a=
ssets took a hit, with Europe=E2=80=99s Stoxx 600 Index tumbling the most i=
n a month and US futures pointing to losses at the open.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fitch=E2=80=99s action echoed one made in 2011=
 by S&amp;P Global Ratings, which was never reversed. Although few investor=
s see Treasuries shedding their status as the safest haven and most reliabl=
e source of collateral, the downgrade is still a spotlight on the worsening=
 US fiscal outlook.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And=C2=A0Sagarika Jaisinghani=C2=A0and Julien =
Ponthus <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32274940.2=
64413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDgtMDIvZ=
G9sbGFyLXMtZHJvcC1vbi1maXRjaC1kb3duZ3JhZGUtdW5saWtlbHktdG8tcGVyc2lzdC1hbmFs=
eXN0cz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwODAyMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3V=
yY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA4MDImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7992f939" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  round up analyst and investor re=
actions</a>, which are all along the lines of =E2=80=9CI guess I am suppose=
d to say something about this downgrade but really it=E2=80=99s not much ne=
ws=E2=80=9D:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mark Dowding, chief investment off=
icer at RBC BlueBay Asset Management LLP:=C2=A0=E2=80=9COn the whole, we do=
n=E2=80=99t see the Fitch downgrade to US as particularly significant. Howe=
ver, it serves as a reminder that there will be heavy ongoing issuance of T=
reasuries on a forward-looking basis and this is something that can weigh o=
n global markets if this prompts a steepening of the yield curve and a rise=
 in the discount rate for longer-dated cashflows.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are a Treasury investor and Fitch is=C2=
=A0<em>reminding=C2=A0</em>you that a lot of Treasury issuance is coming, t=
hat might be a useful service, but it is=C2=A0very much the sort of thing t=
hat you=E2=80=99d expect to be priced into an efficient market. The market =
is not really supposed to react to=C2=A0<em>reminders</em>.<a class=3D"foot=
note-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !importan=
t; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is not very much information content in =
this downgrade. The market for Treasuries is pretty efficient, meaning that=
 the market is generally aware of big issues like =E2=80=9CUS government is=
 polarized=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cthere=E2=80=99s a lot of Treasury debt,=E2=
=80=9D so Fitch saying that is not going to change much. When we last discu=
ssed this, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3227494=
0.264413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMD=
UtMjUvdGhlLXVzLW1pZ2h0LWJlLW9ubHktYWE_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDgwMjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmd=
XRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwODAyJnV0=
bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC9f1a095a" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">I w=
rote</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If I were a ratings agency my rati=
ng on US government debt would not be a semi-arbitrary collection of As. My=
 rating would be =E2=80=9Cthis is US government debt.=E2=80=9D For good and=
 for ill, people mostly know what that means!</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still, I mean, the expectation does seem to be=
 that Fitch will give the US government a rating, and I suppose if it think=
s that the US is overly indebted and dysfunctional, then as a matter of int=
ellectual honesty it ought to downgrade it. The timing is odd but I guess y=
ou have to think hard about this stuff. It is not really an=C2=A0<em>object=
ion=C2=A0</em>to the downgrade to say =E2=80=9Cwell this adds no new inform=
ation to the market.=E2=80=9D The point is not to add new information; the =
point is not to be wrong.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or whatever. Is that the point? What is the po=
int of credit ratings? My general assumption is that the point of ratings i=
s=C2=A0<em>not</em> primarily to tell investors which bonds they should buy=
. My assumption is that the point of ratings is primarily to serve some sor=
t of quasi-regulatory function: Investors choose which bonds to buy, but th=
ey are constrained by mandates or marketing documents or regulation to only=
 buy =E2=80=9Cinvestment-grade=E2=80=9D bonds, and ratings determine which =
bonds are investment-grade. Or you do a derivative trade that requires your=
 counterparty to post collateral, and the counterparty can post whatever co=
llateral she wants as long as it is rated at least AA. Credit ratings are n=
ot there to=C2=A0<em>inform=C2=A0</em>investment decisions, but to <em>cons=
train=C2=A0</em>them, to limit the universe of bonds that an investor is al=
lowed to own.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So you could imagine reading Fitch=E2=80=99s d=
owngrade very differently, not =E2=80=9Chuh, the US has a lot of debt, didn=
=E2=80=99t know that=E2=80=9D but rather =E2=80=9Coh no, I need to dump all=
 of the Treasuries from my Only AAA Rated Bond Fund.=E2=80=9D I don=E2=80=
=99t think you <em>should</em>. I don=E2=80=99t think that there are any ma=
terial parts of the market where investors are allowed to hold Treasuries i=
f they are rated AAA by Fitch, but not if they are rated AA+. (The fact tha=
t Treasuries are rated Aaa by Moody=E2=80=99s, but have been rated AA+ by S=
tandard &amp; Poor=E2=80=99s for more than a decade, makes this especially =
unlikely: Your fund would have to have a rule like=C2=A0=E2=80=9Crated AAA =
by two of the three major ratings agencies.=E2=80=9D) When we last <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32274940.264413/aHR0cHM6L=
